citations:
    citation-affc-jaime-ix:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Jaime IX"
            text_from_source: "You'll see them crowned, and you'll see them die."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Jaime compels Edmure Tully to yield Riverrun by threatening to trebuchet his unborn child and destroy the castle utterly. Edmure agrees and opens the gates. The Blackfish escapes by swimming underwater beneath the Water Gate. Jaime later receives Cersei's desperate letter ('Come at once, I love you, I love you, I love you') and throws it in the fire without reply."
